<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7219] Make it so can connect remotely to a standalone hbase</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7219</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Should be able to connect from a remote client to a standalone instance.  HBase has &apos;localhost&apos; in regionservers file and will write &apos;localhost&apos; to znode for master location which remote client can&apos;t use.  Fix.  This comes up on mailing list w/ some frequency.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12617655">HBASE-7219</key>
            <summary>Make it so can connect remotely to a standalone hbase</summary>
